    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with the tomatoes and cook for 3-4 min, breaking up the <strong>'Nduja</strong> with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Keep the heat medium to avoid the 'Nduja from smoking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a small splash of <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> spicy 'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>to the pan and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> 'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
